---

<DocLayout
  title="deleteWordForward"
  description="How deleteWordForward inputType deletes words forward (Ctrl+Delete) and varies across browsers."
  currentPath={Astro.url.pathname}
>
        <DocSection title="Overview">
          <p class="m-0 mb-4">
            The <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[0.85em]">deleteWordForward</code> inputType is triggered when the user presses <kbd class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-bg-muted rounded text-xs">Ctrl/Cmd + Delete</kbd>. The browser deletes the word after the cursor position (forward word deletion).
          </p>
        </DocSection>

        <DocSection title="Basic Behavior">
          <DocInfoBox title="Scenario: Cursor in middle of word">
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2 text-text-primary">Before (Cursor at position 8)</h4>
                <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-light rounded-md p-3 font-mono text-sm">
                  <div class="text-text-secondary">HTML:</div>
                  <div class="text-text-primary mt-1">&lt;p&gt;Hello <span class="bg-blue-200 dark:bg-blue-900/40 px-1 rounded">|</span>world text&lt;/p&gt;</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2 text-text-primary">After Ctrl/Cmd + Delete</h4>
                <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-light rounded-md p-3 font-mono text-sm">
                  <div class="text-text-secondary">HTML:</div>
                  <div class="text-text-primary mt-1">&lt;p&gt;Hello <span class="bg-blue-200 dark:bg-blue-900/40 px-1 rounded">|</span> text&lt;/p&gt;</div>
                  <div class="text-text-secondary mt-2 text-xs">Entire word "world " deleted</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </DocInfoBox>
        </DocSection>

        <DocSection title="Difference from deleteWordBackward">
          <DocInfoBox>
            <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-text-primary">deleteWordForward (Ctrl/Cmd + Delete)</h4>
                <ul class="m-0 pl-6 text-text-secondary">
                  <li class="mb-1">Deletes word/content <strong>after</strong> cursor</li>
                  <li class="mb-1">Forward word deletion</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-text-primary">deleteWordBackward (Ctrl/Cmd + Backspace)</h4>
                <ul class="m-0 pl-6 text-text-secondary">
                  <li class="mb-1">Deletes word/content <strong>before</strong> cursor</li>
                  <li class="mb-1">Backward word deletion</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </DocInfoBox>
        </DocSection>

        <DocSection title="IME Composition + deleteWordForward">
          <DocAlert type="error" title="⚠️ Critical Issue">
            <p class="m-0 mb-2 text-sm">
              During IME composition, pressing <kbd class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-white/50 dark:bg-black/20 rounded text-xs">Ctrl/Cmd + Delete</kbd> may cancel the composition or delete more than expected. The behavior varies significantly between browsers and IME implementations.
            </p>
            <p class="m-0 text-sm">
              See: <a href="/docs/input-types/deleteContentForward#ime-composition--deletecontentforward" class="text-accent-primary underline">deleteContentForward</a> for similar issues with regular Delete.
            </p>
          </DocAlert>
        </DocSection>

        <DocSection title="Editor-Specific Handling">
          <p class="m-0 mb-4">
            Different editor frameworks handle word-level forward deletion similarly to backward deletion. Here's how major editors implement deleteWordForward:
          </p>

          <EditorExample
            editor="slate"
            title="Word Forward Deletion"
            description="Slate uses Transforms.delete() with word unit (forward):"
            code={`import { Editor, Transforms } from 'slate';

element.addEventListener('beforeinput', (e) => {
  if (e.inputType === 'deleteWordForward') {
    e.preventDefault();
    
    const { selection } = editor;
    if (selection) {
      // Delete word forward
      Transforms.delete(editor, { unit: 'word' });
    }
  }
});`}
            features={[
              '<strong>Transforms.delete:</strong> Uses <code class="bg-bg-surface px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[0.85em]">unit: \'word\'</code> without <code class="bg-bg-surface px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[0.85em]">reverse</code> flag.',
              '<strong>Same API:</strong> Uses same method as backward deletion, just without <code class="bg-bg-surface px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[0.85em]">reverse: true</code>.',
            ]}
          />

          <EditorExample
            editor="prosemirror"
            title="Word Forward Deletion"
            description="ProseMirror uses word boundary detection forward:"
            code={`view.dom.addEventListener('beforeinput', (e) => {
  if (e.inputType === 'deleteWordForward') {
    e.preventDefault();
    const { state, dispatch } = view;
    
    // Extend selection forward to word boundary
    const { $to } = state.selection;
    const wordEnd = $to.endOfWord($to);
    
    if (wordEnd !== null) {
      const tr = state.tr.delete($to.pos, wordEnd.pos);
      dispatch(tr);
    }
  }
});`}
            features={[
              '<strong>Word boundary detection:</strong> Uses <code class="bg-bg-surface px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[0.85em]">endOfWord()</code> to find word end.',
              '<strong>Transaction-based:</strong> Creates transaction to delete word range forward.',
            ]}
          />

          <EditorExample
            editor="draftjs"
            title="Word Forward Deletion"
            description="Draft.js finds word end and deletes:"
            code={`import { EditorState, Modifier } from 'draft-js';

function handleDeleteWordForward(editorState) {
  const contentState = editorState.getCurrentContent();
  const selection = editorState.getSelection();
  
  // Find word end
  const block = contentState.getBlockForKey(selection.getStartKey());
  const text = block.getText();
  const offset = selection.getStartOffset();
  
  // Find word boundary (simplified)
  let wordEnd = offset;
  while (wordEnd < text.length && /\S/.test(text[wordEnd])) {
    wordEnd++;
  }
  
  // Create new selection from cursor to word end
  const newSelection = selection.merge({
    anchorOffset: offset,
    focusOffset: wordEnd,
  });
  
  // Delete selection
  const newContentState = Modifier.removeRange(
    contentState,
    newSelection,
    'forward'
  );
  
  return EditorState.push(
    editorState,
    newContentState,
    'remove-range'
  );
}`}
            features={[
              '<strong>Word boundary detection:</strong> Manually finds word end by scanning forward for whitespace.',
              '<strong>Selection extension:</strong> Extends selection to word boundary before deleting.',
            ]}
          />
        </DocSection>

